<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF4C6AF3F82290631766BCA0" pageId="183" pageNumber="945" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF4C6AF3F82290631766BCA0" blockId="183.[2013,2606,1353,1781]" lastBlockId="183.[1399,2607,1787,3477]" pageId="183" pageNumber="945">
Subgenus Pizonyx; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4C6AF3F71590631758BD65" authorityName="E. Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1806" box="[2281,2392,1594,1623]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="183" pageNumber="945" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albescens">albescens</taxonomicName>
species group. Based on morphology and molecular data, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4C6AF3F7CD90DC16DBBD94" authorityName="Schinz" authorityYear="1821" box="[2097,2267,1669,1702]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="183" pageNumber="944" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigricans">M. nigricans</taxonomicName>
is a complex of undescribed cryptic species. Recent taxonomic revisions of population samples previously identified as 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4C6AF3F9CB90A218E0BC2E" authorityName="Schinz" authorityYear="1821" box="[1591,1760,1787,1820]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="183" pageNumber="944" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigricans">M. nigricans</taxonomicName>
have resulted in new species (e.g. M. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4C6AF3F6E990A2175DBC2E" box="[2325,2397,1787,1820]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="183" pageNumber="945" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lavali">lavali</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4C6AF3F68D90A21427BC2E" box="[2417,2599,1787,1820]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="183" pageNumber="945" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="clydejonesi">M. clydejonesi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4C6AF3FA85917A1855BC76" box="[1401,1621,1827,1860]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="183" pageNumber="945" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="attenboroughi">M. attenboroughi</taxonomicName>
, M. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4C6AF3F969917A1900BC76" box="[1685,1792,1827,1860]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="183" pageNumber="945" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="handleyi">handleyi</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4C6AF3F8AC917A1603BC76" authorityName="Moratelli &amp; Wilson" authorityYear="2011" box="[1872,2051,1827,1860]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="183" pageNumber="945" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="diminutus">M. diminutus</taxonomicName>
) and raising subspecies to species level (e.g. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4C6AF3FA3F9113186FBC59" authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1914" box="[1475,1647,1866,1899]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="183" pageNumber="944" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caucensis">M. caucensis</taxonomicName>
). Nevertheless, thorough taxonomic revision of all populations currently referred to as 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4C6AF3F9649128193DBCA0" authorityName="Schinz" authorityYear="1821" box="[1688,1853,1905,1938]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="183" pageNumber="944" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigricans">M. nigricans</taxonomicName>
is needed. Four subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
